--- !u!114 &114677076708776770
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 1
  m_PrefabParentObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInternal: {fileID: 100100000}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1737069546172976}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 708705254, guid: f70555f144d8491a825f0804e09c671c, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
    m_TypeName: UnityEngine.UI.MaskableGraphic+CullStateChangedEvent, UnityEngine.UI,
      Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 10102, guid: 0000000000000000e000000000000000, type: 0}
    m_FontSize: 14
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 10
    m_MaxSize: 40
    m_Alignment: 0
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "<b>Getting Started</b>\r\nWelcome to Star Trader. This is a simple little
    game where you have a cargo ship and you can trade commodities between space stations
    while trying to avoid pirates who want to plunder your loot.\r\nYou can bring
    this screen up at any time by pressing the ? button on your ship computer.\r\n\r\n<b>Controls</b>\r\nSpace
    - Switch between controlling the space craft or the ships computer.\r\nDirect
    Control Mode\r\nWASD - Move the ship forward, back, left and right etc.\r\nQE
    - Move the ship up and down.\r\nMouse - Rotate the ship in the direction you want
    and allow for aiming shots.\r\nMouse 1 - Fire Beam Weapons\r\nMouse 2 - Fire Rockets\r\nB
    - Brake\r\n\r\n<i>Ship Computer</i>\r\nFrom the ship computer you can interact
    with it by clicking buttons on the screen when they are available.\r\nOpen Coms
    - When you are in range of a space station you can open a communication channel
    to trade, upgrade your ship and refuel etc.\r\nCargo Bay - You can view the contents
    of your cargo bay.\r\n? - Opens up this help screen.\r\nTake control - Changes
    the control mode to direct control mode.\r\n\r\n<b>Movement</b>\r\nYou need to
    keep in mind when moving around space that there is very little gravity. This
    means your ship will keep going in the direction its going till you apply force
    in the opposite direction or the break.\r\nAnother thing to be careful of when
    moving is everytime you apply thrust with WASDQ or E you expend fuel. Braking
    on the other hand expends a huge ammount of fuel. If you run out of speed will
    start to drop to a crawl.\r\nYou can also travel between systems by making use
    of handy jump gates that are scattered all over the place.\r\n\r\n<b>Combat</b>\r\nYour
    ship is equiped with both beam weapons and rockets. Beam weapons can be used continously
    but do very little damage while rockets only have a few shots but can damage multiple
    targets at once. You can restock rockets at space stations.\r\nYou also have the
    ability to upgrade your ship at space stations which allow you to take more damage
    and do more.\r\n\r\n<b>Next Moves</b>\r\nNow you have read the tutorial you should
    be ready to play the game. Adventure forth through the portal ahead and try trading
    with the space station you will find there.\r\n"
